reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A good phone case for a good value
reviews.reviewText: I bought a new iPhone after breaking my last phone, I'm usually a rebel without a cause when it comes to phones and I just don't like cases, however, after breaking my last iPhone I decided to just buy a case. I'm not too particular to any brands so when I saw the styling of this one I quite liked it. I ordered it, it came one day early, and I was quite happy with my purchase. The rubber sides don't have too much grip where you can't comfortably pull your phone out of your pocket or slide it in, but there is enough to hold it without worry of dropping it or having it slip. The camera bump leaves a generous amount of room for the cameras, so placing it down on a table or any flat surfaces doesn't have you concerned if you're scraping the camera lenses.Overall the durability of it is nice, I dropped my phone (not on purpose, mind you) a few times and every time the case absorbs the energy and the phone is fine. I'd highly recommend this case for the value, and the style.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great quality and protection
reviews.reviewText: Really impressed with this phone case. The case is a hard plastic, but very durable - feels expensive. I have the green and it's so beautiful. The green matches my green iphone 13 mini. The camera lenses are also protected by the lip of the case. The case doesn't fit flush in the front leaving enough room for protection - as in if you drop it, the glass is protected. I have dropped my phone a couple of times since receiving and my phone is still in perfect condition. I do have a screen protector. I feel like this case will last for awhile - especially for the price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Protective but not too bulky.
reviews.reviewText: I needed a MagSafe compatible case and I’d been using a bulky and expensive Otterbox case which was fine aside from not being MagSafe compatible. This case was nicely priced and understated, which I like. It’s a nice snug fit and is raised in all the right places so as to offer really good protection, but is not too bulky. I am using it on an iPhone 13 Mini. I use the Mini because small size is one of the most important things about the phone to me. When I put it in this case, I realized how bulky the other one was. I drop my phone a lot and this one does just as good a job protecting it. It’s exceeded my expectations, I’m very pleased with it.
